The paper discusses deep learning architectures for face recognition in video surveillance, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.MM) and deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the challenges of face recognition in uncontrolled scenarios, which may involve issues related to security and privacy (cs.CR) as well as image retrieval (cs.IR).
